    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-12-21</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-02-03T20:01:36Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Hurricane Election Relief Act of 2005 - Directs the Election Assistance Commission to make a grant to each state for the purpose of: (1) restoring and replacing supplies, materials, records, equipment, and technology used in the administration of federal elections which were damaged, destroyed, or dislocated as a result of Hurricane Katrina or Hurricane Rita; and (2) ensuring the full participation in such elections by individuals displaced as a result of Hurricane Katrina or Hurricane Rita. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>82</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-02-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed Senate without amendment</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-02-21T21:07:33Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version is repeated here.)</b></p><p>Hurricane Election Relief Act of 2005 - Directs the Election Assistance Commission to make a grant to each state for the purpose of: (1) restoring and replacing supplies, materials, records, equipment, and technology used in the administration of federal elections which were damaged, destroyed, or dislocated as a result of Hurricane Katrina or Hurricane Rita; and (2) ensuring the full participation in such elections by individuals displaced as a result of Hurricane Katrina or Hurricane Rita. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
